This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the analysis of large datasets of high resolution images. It may also belong to the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it focuses on managing data on clusters of hybrid computing nodes. Additionally, the paper introduces a data structure abstraction, which could fall under the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also discusses different data management strategies and data I/O implementations, which could be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper may also belong to the numerical analysis (cs.NA) sub-category as it deals with the efficient management of data on distributed memory machines.
